The paper deals with image reconstruction using deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of trainable models, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sparsity-driven regularization, which could potentially fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the performance gains achieved through the inclusion of traditional regularization techniques, which could be relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
